Commentary.Commentary: We are back for Australia's reply. They trail by 189 runs. The two umpires make their way out on the field. The South Africa players are seen to be in a huddle near the ropes. Meanwhile, David Warner and Usman Khawaja strides out to the middle to open for the hosts. It will be Kagiso Rabada to start with the new ball.
... SECOND INNINGS ...

The whole of Melbourne Cricket Ground is on its feet here to applaud a stunning spell from Cameron Green who walks out with the ball in hand after recording his first ever five-wicket haul in Test cricket that too it comes in a Boxing Day Test match. It couldn't have gotten any better than this for Green. This session started completely on a different note, as the pair of Kyle Verreynne and Marco Jansen played a really good knock. Both players scored their respective half-centuries, the only two batters who stood out for the Proteas. Although, once this stand was broken. The tail was ripped apart single-handedly by Cameron Green. Australia would be really happy with the position they are in. Once again South Africa find themselves in a tricky situation. They need a solid start with the ball in hand and they have a capable enough bowling attack to trouble the batters. Do join us for the second innings shortly.

OUT! TIMBER! FIVE-FER FOR GREEN! He has destroyed the South African lower middle-order here. This time he bowls it fuller and around off, straightens a bit, Lungi Ngidi makes room and tries to drive again, but misses the ball completely and loses his off pole. South Africa have been bowled out for 189!
Commentary.Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Full and on off, Lungi Ngidi drives it past mid off and gets a couple of runs.
Cameron Green bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, Lungi Ngidi ducks underneath it.
Full and on middle, Anrich Nortje tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, full and on off, Lungi Ngidi knocks it to the off side.
On off, defended.
Darts this one full and on middle, Lungi Ngidi blocks it out.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! Nathan Lyon gets his first wicket now. He filghts this one up, full and on off, Keshav Maharaj looks to take him on and goes for the big shot, but he miscues it badly as the ball flies in the air behind mid off where Pat Cummins trackbacks a bit, settles under it and completes the catch. South Africa are just throwing their wickets away here.
Commentary.Howout: c Pat Cummins b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up, full and on middle, Keshav Maharaj leans on and blocks it out.
Flatter, short and on off, Keshav Maharaj looks to poke at it, but misses it completely.

Drinks break! Woah! Cameron Green has turned this game on its head now. He picked up three wickets in a flash to put South Africa in a precarious position after a solid fightback. Australia would be hoping to restrict the Proteas under 200 here. Anrich Nortje is the new batter in.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Cameron Green gets another one in this over! He picks up his fourth wicket and Australia have made a good comeback in this game. Green bowls this short of a length again and on of, Kagiso Rabada is in two minds whether to play it or leave it, and just keeps his bat there hanging. The ball takes the inside edge and rattle onto the stumps. Kagiso Rabada just stays there in disappointment. South Africa eight down now!
Commentary.Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Short of a length and on off, Kagiso Rabada lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Full again and on off, Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards covers.
FOUR! Kagiso Rabada opens his account with a boundary! This is full and outside off, Kagiso Rabada steers it in the gap and towards the third man fence for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Kagiso Rabada guides it towards point.
Kagiso Rabada comes in at number 9.

EDGED AND GONE! Cameron Green with a double strike here! He sends both the set batters back to the hut in consecutive overs. He serves this on a fuller length and on the fifth stump line, Marco Jansen goes for the drive on the up without any footwork, but the shape away takes the outside edge of his bat and goes towards the keeper where Alex Carey takes a comfortable catch. Marco Jansen played well, but he has to make that long walk back. South Africa lose their seventh.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Full and outside off, Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.
Keshav Maharaj is the new man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Cameron Green finally gets the breakthrough! Australian players are relieved to see the back of Kyle Verreynne here. Cameron Green bowls this on a good length and just around off, Kyle Verreynne prods forward to defend, but gets a thin outside edge towards Steven Smith at slips who makes no mistake. The huge partnership is finally broken and South Africa are six down now.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Cameron Green

Pat Cummins thinks it is close enough and takes the review. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball, in the channel of uncertainty. It shapes away a bit. The Australian fielders though seem to be exicted but it was cut short after the review confirms that there was no bat involved.

Half-a-chance! Shouts of catch but it lands safe. It is pushed through quicker, around middle and leg. Marco Jansen comes down the track and gets an inside edge on his pads. The ball goes aerially to the right of the bowler, but it lands safely, even the short leg could not react quicker.

We are back for the last session! The Australian players are making their way out in the middle followed by the two batters, Marco Jansen and Kyle Verreynne. Nathan Lyon to continue after the break.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

This has been a really good session for the Proteas. They were 4 wickets down when they came into the post-Lunch session with just 58 runs on the scoreboard. Since then, they have managed to rack up around 86 runs in 27 overs thanks to a gritty partnership between Kyle Verreynne and Marco Jansen of 77 runs. Marco Jansen faced almost 93 deliveries for his 38 runs. He is showing his composure at the crease and also played a perfect supporting role for Kyle Verreynne. The Proteas have put up a solid fightback and would be hoping to continue on their merry in the final session of Day 1. Australia though could only found success through Starc in the afternoon session. Nathan Lyon also troubled the batters with his spin but still remains wicketless. Has the conditions now improved for batting? Or will Australia come all gun-blazing in the post-Tea session? To find out how things pan out, do join us at 10 am IST (4.30 am GMT) for an intriguing session of cricket.

Length, on off, tucked to the leg side.
JAFFA! It is a length ball, outside off, it shapes away a touch off the deck. Marco Jansen tries to block it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Marco Jansen ducks under it.

IN THE AIR! It lands safely though. It is a short ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne tries to pull it away without any foot movement. The ball takes a thick outside edge and goes high in the air towards square leg. Alex Carey gives it a chase from behind the sticks but could not get there in time. One taken.
Mitchell Starc bangs in a bouncer, on leg, Marco Jansen ducks under it.
Fuller one and on off, Marco Jansen drives it past short covers for a brace and gets off the mark.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and on off, angling away, Marco Jansen looks to play at it but get beaten on the outside edge.
Marco Jansen walks out to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT!! Mitchell Starc gets the first wicket in the post-Lunch session and the crowd is loving it. A full-length ball, angling across, outside off. Khaya Zondo tries to drive it through the line but does so aerially. It goes to the left of extra cover. Marnus Labuschagne places there dives to his left and takes a sharp low catch to break this stand.
Commentary.Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: This full delivery is driven through covers for a couple now.

How has this missed the stumps? Khaya Zondo almost chops on! It is a length ball, angled across the right-hander. Khaya Zondo tries to leave it away but is a tad late. The ball hit the deck and luckily, it goes past the stumps.
Pat Cummins gets his fourth maiden so far. It is a length ball, on fifth stump. Kyle Verreynne gets behind the line and blocks it out to safety.
Length and on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it to covers off the front foot.
Another dot! A length ball, around the hips. Kyle Verreynne comes inside the line and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Too full and straight, Kyle Verreynne defends this full delivery back to the bowler.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne stays back and tucks it to the right of the bowler.
This is a length ball that lands outside off and nips in a bit. Kyle Verreynne closes the face and blocks it away.
Yes, he does! Second maiden for the seamer. It is full and on off. Zondo drives it straight to the man at mid off.
Make it five! Good length, on the pads, Zondo clips it towards mid-wicket. Will Starc be able to complete his maiden over?
Four dots in a row! It is a sharp bouncer, around off. Zondo sways away from the line of delivery.
On off, blocked out to safety.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, angling across the right-hander. Khaya Zondo looks to ride the bounce and cut it away but misses.
Starc serves a short ball, outside off. Zondo leaves it alone for the keeper.
Touch short, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne lets it be. Just three runs off the over.
On a length, on off. This one stays low. Kyle Verreynne gets his blade down in time to defend it out.
Zondo flicks this full delivery into mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Very full, wide of off. Zondo hits it through the line and drives it through the off side. The batters take two with ease.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Zondo shuffles and taps it to covers.
Full length, around leg. Zondo blocks it towards mid on.
FOUR! Top placement. It is a  half-volley, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne gets on his front foot and squeezes it past backward point for a boundary.
Slightly shorter, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne tries to go for the cut shot but gets beaten in the process.
Make that four! It is a length ball, on off. This one stays low a touch and nips into the batter from outside off. Kyle Verreynne comes forward and defends it out.
Three dots in a row! It is overpitched, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to the off side, not in the gap though.
Kyle Verreynne stays back to this full delivery and defends it to the leg side.
Mitchell Starc starts with a full one, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards mid on.

We are back for the second session! The players are making their way out in the middle now. Khaya Zondo and Kyle Verreynne come out to continue their innings. Mitchell Starc to start with the ball after the break.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The South African top order was unable to find their rhythm agianst a fiery pace attack of the Aussies. This hasn't been a brightest of starts for the visitors and they need a special knock here if they are to get safe here. It will be interesting to see how things pan out. Australia would be hoping to end the innings as soon as possible. Mitchell Starc, Cameron Green and Scott Boland took a wicket each to put the hosts on top. Do join us at 7.40 am IST (2.10 am GMT) for the post-Lunch session. Will South Africa be able to turn things around? Or will Australia continue to destroy the opposition with the ball in hand?

Lunch Break! It is Australia that head back into the break as the happier side with the hosts picking up 4 wickets in 24 overs for just 58 runs. South Africa are way behind in this game on Day 1 and need a miracle to get them out of this hole. They will need their lower-middle order to turn up if the occasion asks for it.
On a length and on off, Khaya Zondo strokes it towards point. That will be Lunch!
Pat Cummins bangs this short and on off, Khaya Zondo sways out of the line of it.
Fuller one and on off, Khaya Zondo drills it back towards the bowler.
Pat Cummins continues to bowl on a good length, outside off again, Khaya Zondo shoulders arms.
Length again and outside off, Khaya Zondo leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, Khaya Zondo moves across and blocks it out.
Kyle Verreynne is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Two in two balls for Australia and they are well and truly on top here! Temba Bavuma goes back to the hut for a low score. Mitchell Starc bowls this on a hard length and around off with some away movement, Temba Bavuma looks to poke at it from his crease, but only manages to get a thin outside edge towards the keeper where Alex Carey takes a good catch moving to his right. South Africa four down before Lunch now!
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Khaya Zondo walks out to bat now.

OUT! RUN OUT! A disaster for South Africa! Dean Elgar has gifted his wicket with a lapse of judgement here. Mitchell Starc bowl this on a hard length and on off, Dean Elgar punches it to the right of mid off and set off for the run. However, Marnus Labuschagne there and runs onto the ball in a flash, picks it up and hits bullseye at the non-striker's end and Elgar is well short of his crease. The replays confirms the same. South Africa in trouble now just before Lunch.
Commentary.Howout: run out (Marnus Labuschagne)

Commentary.Commentary: Not sure what Elgar is upto here! This is back of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar thinks about the pull shot, but decides against and it awkwardly pushes it towards covers.
Short of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar stays back and mistimes his push towards mid off.
Length again and on middle, Dean Elgar works it towards mid on again.
On a length and on middle, Dean Elgar knocks it towards mid on.
Full and on off, Temba Bavuma drives it towards the bowler where Pat Cummins goes down and gets a hand to it as he parries it towards mid off.
Back of a length and on off, extra bounce again, Temba Bavuma watches it through and blocks it with the outer half of his bat to the off side.
Fuller one and outside off, Temba Bavuma lets it go to the keeper.
Short of a length and on middle, Temba Bavuma defends it well this time.
This is on a good length and outside off, Temba Bavuma looks to block it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Wow...that could have easily been a wicket! Pat Cummins bowls this on a hard length and on off, gets some extra bounce of the surface, Temba Bavuma does really well to keep it down as he gets hit on his gloves.
Pat Cummins (5-1-15-0) is back on.
Back of a length and on middle, Temba Bavuma tucks it towards square leg for a single and gets off the mark.
Fuller one and on the pads, Dean Elgar nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a hard length and around off, Dean Elgar looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar gets hurried and blocks it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, Dean Elgar works it towards mid on.
On a length and outside off, Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Temba Bavuma comes out to the middle now. Also, Mitchell Starc comes back into the attack.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cameron Green strikes now! He bowls this short of a length again and around off, Theunis de Bruyn stays there and goes for the pull shot, but gets an top edge as the ball flies in the air and behind the keeper. Alex Carey calls for it, settles under and takes a good catch. There was absolutely no need of that shot and Theunis de Bruyn has thrown his wicket away here. South Africa two down now!
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary.Commentary: Extra bounce! Cameron Green bowls this back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn looks to upper cut it, but gets beaten by the extra bounce from the surface.
Short of a length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone once again.
This is on a good length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn works it towards mid-wicket.
Goes a bit fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
On a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn knocks it towards mid off.

FOUR! Good shot! Scott Boland comes around the wicket and serves this full, on middle, angling in, Dean Elgar stays there and drives it towards the vacant long off fence for a boundary. That also brings up 5000 runs for Elgar in Test cricket.
Back of a length and around off, Dean Elgar blocks it out to the off side.
This is on a good length and on off, Dean Elgar looks to play at it, but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards slip cordon.
Fuller one and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn works it towards mid on for a single.
Scott Boland once again bowls this on a good length and on off, shaping in a bit, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Short of a length and on leg, Dean Elgar helps it towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller one and on off, Theunis de Bruyn strokes it towards mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn steers it towards point.
This is on a good length and just ouside off, Theunis de Bruyn lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Two in a row! This is a poor delivery though as Green bowls this on a hard length and on the pads, Theunis de Bruyn tickles it towards the fine leg fence for another boundary.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn stays there and shows the full face of the bat to drive it straight past the bowler for a boundary.

Almost a wicket on the first ball for Green! He starts with a full delivery, outside off, Dean Elgar slices it uppishly towards point where Nathan Lyon dives to his left but only manages to get finger tips of his left hand. They cross.
Two maiden overs in row then! Scott Boland serves this on a hard length and on off, angling in, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Another one! This is on a good length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
Scott Boland is sticking to his good length and outside off line, Theunis de Bruyn is happy to let it go to the keeper once again.
Full again and around off, Theunis de Bruyn watches it carefully and makes a good leave.
This is full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn defends it in front of point.
Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and on the fifth stump line, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
A maiden over! Nathan Lyon bowls this short and on off, Dean Elgar taps it but finds covers again.
Another dot! This is flighted, full and on off, Dean Elgar drives it towards cover again.
Shorter in length and on off, Dean Elgar punches it towards covers.
Floated, full and on off, turning away, Dean Elgar leans on and slices it a bit towards covers.
Short and well outside off, Dean Elgar cuts it but straight to point. He missed out there as this was a poor delivery.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Dean Elgar drives it towards mid on.
This is on a good length and around off, Theunis de Bruyn leans on and lets it go to the keeper.
Goes fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn is solid in his defense.
Short of a length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn cuts it through point for a couple of runs.
Full again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn guides it towards gully again.
This is a touch fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn goes to drive it but gets an outside edge and the ball goes on the bounce towards gully.
Scott Boland comes 'over the wicket and bowls this on a hard length, on off, angling in, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Theunis de Bruyn gets off the mark now! This is short and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn moves onto his back foot quickly and pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Flighted, full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn leans on and defends it down the pitch.
Tossed up, full and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
Darts this one full and on the pads, Dean Elgar tucks it through square leg for a single.
Floated, short and on off, Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Flatter, short and on middle, grips and turns a long way to the leg side, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone and the leg slip parries it behind the keeper. A bye is taken.
BEATEN! Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and around off, straightens a bit after hitting the deck, Dean Elgar gets squared up and gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length and on off, Dean Elgar defends it towards point.
Back of a length and on off, Dean Elgar pushes it towards covers.
FOUR! Nice shot! Scott Boland serves this full again and on off, Dean Elgar stays there and drives it well wide of short covers and towards the long off fence for a boundary.
This is pitched up, on off, Dean Elgar drills it wide of short covers where the fielder dives to his right to make a one-handed stop.

Oh..this is close! Scott Boland bowls this back of a length and on middle, angling in, Dean Elgar looks to block it out but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls towards the stumps. It just kisses the bottom of the off pole, but there is not enough power to knock the bails off. Elgar survives.
A single to end the over as this short delivery is forced to the left of point by Elgar.
Shortish and on off again, Dean Elgar knocks it off the back foot towards point.
Nathan Lyon continues with his shorter length, on off, Dean Elgar steers it towards point.
Shorter again and outside off, Dean Elgar goes on his back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a brace.
Floated, short and on off, turning away a bit, Dean Elgar blocks it to the off side.
Nathan Lyon starts with a tossed up delivery, short and on off, Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Change. Time for some spin now as Nathan Lyon comes into the attack.
Fuller one, on middle, swinging in, Theunis de Bruyn misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads towards the leg side. End of a successful over for the Aussies!
On a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn guides it with the outer half of his bat towards point.

Drinks break! South Africa started well with the blade, but could not remain unscathed in the opening hour of the morning session to spoil their progress so far. Australia would be hoping to restrict the opposition to build partnerships. It will be Theunis de Bruyn to come in at number 3. `

OUT! TAKEN! Scott Boland draws first blood! The crowd is going absolutely berserk over here. Scott Boland bowls another good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away again, Sarel Erwee this time goes for the drive away from his body, but gets an outside edge towards the slip cordon where Usman Khawaja takes a sharp low catch. Sarel Erwee is not happy with himself as he could have easliy left this one alone. South Africa lose their first!
Commentary.Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: BEAUTY! Scott Boland serves this on a hand length and on the sixth stump line, shaping away a shy bit, Sarel Erwee looks to block it out, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Goes a touch fuller and around leg, Dean Elgar nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length just outside off, Dean Elgar lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Sarel Erwee gets pinged high on his pads.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee moves to 18. Very full, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee gets on his front foot and drives it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
Overpitched, wide of off. Dean Elgar drives it through covers for a single.
Short ball, going down leg. Dean Elgar gets inside the line and tries to chase it but misses.
Full length, on off. Elgar blocks it back to Pat Cummins.
Good length, anglded into the batter, on off. Dean Elgar defends it out on his front foot.
Fuller, shaped back into the batter. Sarel Erwee knocks it back to the bowler. A tidy start by Boland.
Slightly short, on off. Elgar taps it to cover and scampers across for a quick single. It could've been a risky run.
Good length, wide of off. Left alone.
Full and on off, pushed to extra covers.
A single now as Sarel Erwee knocks this full ball into covers.
Scott Boland comes 'round the wicket and goes short, wide of off. Sarel Erwee cuts it to point but straight to the fielder.
Scott Boland replaces Mitchell Starc.
Pat Cummins records his first maiden of the innings, Good length, on off. Dean Elgar keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it out.
Too straight, attacking the pads. Elgar pushes it out to safety.
Fuller, on off. Dean Elgar drives it to the right of the bowler.
Pat Cummins angles this into the pads. Dean Elgar looks to tuck it away but he gets a thick inside edge on his pads.
Around off, defended out.
Pat Cummins dishes a length ball, on fifth stump, nips in a bit late. Dean Elgar trusts the bounce and makes a solid leave.
Just a single off the over. Fraction short, wide outside off. Elgar has no shot to offer.
This is in the channel, swinging away. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, on top of off. Sarel Erwee gets on his front foot and defends it out solidly.
Good length, outside off, moving away. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
This is full and on off. Elgar pushes it to cover for one.
A loud appeal for caught behind is turned down. There was surely some noise on the way. It is a length ball, in the channel. It shapes away a touch and Erwee gets beatan on the outside edge.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! It is touch full, on leg. Sarel Erwee stays back and clips it over mid-wicket for another boundary.
FOUR! This one flies past the keeper. Fraction short, sliding down leg. Sarel Erwee stays back and pulls it past the diving keeper for four runs.
Fuller in length, on off, pushed out.
This is outside off once again. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
Good length, in the channel, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Elgar hangs back and tries to flick it away. He gets it back to the bowler off his pads.
It is full and wide outside off. Sarel Erwee leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for three runs.
Mitchell Starc makes a loud appeal once again. It is much fuller, on middle and leg. Erwee tries to flick it away but misses.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Sarel Erwee takes a blow high on his pads. Mitchell Starc appeals but the umpire shows no interest.
Good length, around off. Erwee blocks it into covers.
Length, on fourth stump. Elgar kets it be.

DROPPED! A tough chance nonetheless. It is a full-length ball, on off. Dean Elgar tries to flick it away but miscues it to the left of the bowler. It is in the air for a short while but Pat Cummins could not make the most of it.
Dean Elgar blocks this length ball back to the bowler.
Outside off, onf ifth stump, angling away. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
This length ball is pushed to covers for one.
Touch fuller, on leg stump. Sarel Erwee tries to flick it through the leg side but takes a huge blow high on his pads.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar.
BEATEN! An outswinger, wide of off. Dean Elgar tries to block it out but gets beaten in the process.

Sarel Erwee opens his account with a single. It is full, on middle and leg. Sarel Erwee plays the on drive and gets it to the right of mid on. Pat Cummins moves to that side and makes a solid stop with a dive. The batters take one.
Length, on leg. Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket and gets across for a quick single.
Shorter, wide of off. Elgar is happy with a sighter here as he leaves it alone.
An outswinging delivery, fuller, wide of off. Dean Elgar lets it sail past him.

Just a single off the over then! An excellent start by Cummins. It is a length ball, angled across outside off. The ball nips in a touch off the deck. Although, Sarel Erwee reads the bounce well and makes the leave.
Sarel Erwee is yet to get off the mark here. It is on a good length, on off. Erwee closes the face and blocks it to short leg.
Make that three! Pat Cummins serves a short ball, down leg. Sarel Erwee lets it be as it too far.
Two dots on the trot! This is on a good length, in the channel. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms.
A dot now! Full and on off, angling across. Erwee blocks it out with a straight bat.
This is on a good length, on leg stump. This one skids through. Dean Elgar gets it behind square off the outer half. They cross for one.
Pat Cummins to share the attack with Mitchell Starc.
Mitchell Starc ends his first over with a full delivery, around off, nipping away. Sarel Erwee gets behind the line and blocks it out.
This is full straying on the pads, Dean Elgar stays back and clips it through the gap at mid-wicket. They take three before the fielder chases it down.
A length ball, outside off, moving away. Elgar has no shot to offer.

Dean Elgar and South Africa are off the mark now! It is too full and straight down leg. Dean Elgar clips it past Head at short leg. They take two with ease as the fielder at deep square leg cuts it out.
On a good length, width on offer. Dean Elgar shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
Shape and bounce straightaway for the left-arm seamer. It is full, wide of off, moving away with some extra bounce. Dean Elgar keeps his bat to himself.

We are all set for some Boxing Day Test action! The Australian players are in a huddle just outside the boundary ropes and now they are taking their respective field positions. They are followed by the two South African openers, Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee who are making their way out in the middle. The new ball has been handed over to Mitchell Starc and he is raring to go. Let's play...

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee, Theunis de Bruyn (In for Rassie van der Dussen), Temba Bavuma, Khaya Zondo, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Marco Jansen, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi.

Australia (Unchanged Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Scott Boland.
TOSS - The coin goes up in the air and Pat Cummins calls it right. Australia have decided to BOWL first.

Australia, on the other emerged victorious in the first Test, but it was not an easy ride for them too.  Their bowlers set up the perfect platform for them, but that was not going to be enough and in the end it was the gritty knock of Travis Head that proved to be the difference. Also, this will be the 100th Test for David Warner and the 100th time these two sides meet in the longest format. So, they will want to mark this occasion with another win and seal the series. Will they be able to do it? Or will the Proteas fight back and get something out of this game? Let's find out together. Toss and team news in a bit.

South Africa did not have the best time with the bat in the first Test but they still put up a decent fight as their pacers enjoyed bowling in the favourable conditions. But if they want something out of this one then players like Dean Elgar, Sarel Erwee and Rassie van der Dussen need to take up more responsibility in the batting order. The last time the Proteas faced the Aussies in a Boxing Day Test at the M.C.G, it was in 2008 and they came out on top quite comfortably in the end. They will want to repeat that feat here too.

Hello and a warm welcome folks! It is almost time for an exciting Boxing Day Test encounter between Australia and South Africa at the M.C.G. The atmosphere should be electrifying and we can expect another thrilling contest between the two big heavyweights.  The Aussies will want to wrap up the series in this game and strengthen their top spot in the WTC' 2021-23 cycle while it it is a must-win situation for the Proteas to keep their hopes of qualifying for the WTC'23 Final alive.
... Day 1, Session 1 ...

We are back for the second innings of South Africa! They trail by 386 runs and will have to put on a much improved batting performance. The two umpires are out in the middle followed by the Australian players. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee are the two openers for South Africa. Mitchell Starc to start proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
... THIRD INNINGS ...

Australia have taken a massive lead thanks to the double hundred from David Warner, a maiden-Test hundred from Alex Carey and some fine knocks from Cameron Green, Steven Smith and Travis Head. They will be happy with their perfomace considering the fact that they will be short of bowling options owning to injuries to Cameron Green and Mitchell Starc for the South African second innings. South Africa have a huge task on their hands and will need to bat their skins out if they want to get anything from here. Their main aim for the third session will be to see it out without losing wickets while the hosts will look to make early inroads and put the Proteas under more pressure. It will be an exciting session. Join us for the all the action at 10.15 am IST (4.45 am GMT).

Halt! Mitchell Starc has been hit on the helmet and he will be needing a replacement. Well, he will not be needing a replacement as Pat Cummins has declared the innings and it will also be Tea on Day 3. Australia finish on 575/8 and they have a massive lead of 386 runs. This afternoon session belonged to the batters and there were a couple of milestones as well. Alex Carey registered his maiden Test hundred in front of his family and it will be a special moment for him as he achieved it in the Boxing Day Test. Cameron Green also completed his half-century and it has been a fighting knock from him considering the fact he has a broken finger. South Africa, on the other failed to get any rhythm and were punished for it. They did create a few half chances but the luck was not on their side. Marco Jansen finally got rewarded for his efforts when sent Carey back to the hut, but they still couldn't bowl out the Aussies. However just a few moments before Tea, Pat Cummins gave the signal and declared the innings.
OUCH! That would hurt. Jansen bangs in a short ball, on middle. Starc looks to pull it away but it gets pinged on his helmet.
A full toss, on off. Green pushes it to mid on for a single.
Short ball, on off. Green defends it out watchfully.
It is full, on middle and leg. Starc whips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fraction short, outside off. Starc looks to chase it but misses.
Short and on off, defended with a straight bat.
A short ball, on off. This one climbs on the batter. Green hops and blocks it out.
It is full, sliding down leg. Starc clips it through square leg for a single.
Length and on off, defended out.
SIX! All the way! It is a short ball, on the body, Starc swivels and smokes it over the square leg fence for a biggie.
It is full, on the pads, Starc flicks it to deep square leg for two runs.
On of, defended out.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, wide of off. Green slashes and misses.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Green ducks under it.
On off, blocked out.
Short, outside off, left alone.

FOUR! A fighting innings from Green. He gets his half-ton with an injured fingure here. It is short, outside off. Green stays back and slaps it through point for four runs. The crowd is on its feet here.
A bouncer now, ducked under.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a bouncer, on middle, Mitchell Starc sways away from it.
This is on a hard length and on leg, Mitchell Starc looks to block it out but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards gully.
A slower one now, on a length and on middle, Cameron Green flicks it towards square leg for a run.

The afternoon session on the moving day is set to begin. Alex Carey and Cameron Green walk out with their blade. Soon, the South African players take the field as well. It will be Kagiso Rabada to start with the ball.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

It has been a quite eventful session for South Africa. The conditions were quite better than Day 2 for the bowlers and boy, did they not feast on this wicket. Anrich Nortje picked a couple of wickets to revive the hopes of the visitors. Later, Kagiso Rabada and Lungi Ngidi chipped in with a wicket as well. The bowlers have their task cut out now and would hope to get rid of the remaining batters without too much damage. Do join us at 7.40 am IST (2.10 am GMT), to find out howthings pan out in the post-Lunch session.

The hosts could not continue on their merry way, as Anrich Nortje came into the attack and got rid of Head and Warner on consecutive deiveries. One might've thought that Australia would find it difficult to get near the 300-run mark but a solid and composed knock from Alex Carey sees them with a healthy lead here. Australia still have three wickets in hand and would be hoping to bat for as long as possible.

Australia head into the Lunch break with a lead of 290 runs. The Aussies managed to score 93 runs in the morning session on moving day with the loss of four wickets. South Africa would be a bit disappointed with the way they bowled at the fag end of the session.

Drinks! Cameron Green is the new batter in at the crease. Also, the umpire signals for a drinks break as well. This has been a solid session so far for the Proteas, They have been able to pick up quick wickets and put some pressure on the opposition. South Africa will be hoping to get rid of the tail-enders as soon as possible. They will want to break the stand between Carey and Green before they do anymore damage.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada strikes now! South Africa take a good review here and Pat Cummins becomes the latest victim. Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and on the fifth stump line, Pat Cummins looks to block it out, but gets the slightest of outside edges through to the keeper where Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake. There is an appeal for the catch but the finger stays down. However, Dean Elgar goes for the review where there is nothing on the Hotspot but Snicko shows a spike when the ball passes the bat. The onfield decison is changed and Australia lose their sixth.
